lated US financial system, these days, is rather hostile to certain =0Asort=
s of commodities dealings. (The ones involving Russia or Venezuela.) If =0A=
someone came to you with =E2=80=9Cdollars, but not through the US financial=
 system,=E2=80=9D =0Ayou might find that appealing.=0A=0ABut this mental mo=
del is incomplete. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Odd Lots podcast has a nice =0Aminis=
eries on the story of the Eurodollar, told by Lev Menand and Josh Younger, =
=0Athat clarified my mental model. Eurodollarsare =E2=80=9Cdollars, but not=
 through the US =0Afinancial system,=E2=80=9D dollar-denominated liabilitie=
s of foreign banks that arenot =0Anecessarily backed by dollar-denominated =
assets. (LikeTether <> used to be <>!) =0AAnyway it is a good series and I =
learned a lot; you can listen toPart 1 <>, =0APart 2 <> and Part 3 <> at th=
ose links.=0A=0A=0AThings happen=0A=0A Morgan Stanley <> Profit Doubles Wit=
